{
  "stem": "22972.2",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "I don't think-- my father was not important enough for our phone to be bugged, but you didn't know.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "Telephones were bugged all over the city.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "Help-- domestics-- were paid to inform.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "At that point, of course, we were no longer allowed to have multiple help.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "We were only permitted to have one in help, and that one had to be an alte Schachtel-- an old, useless woman.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "My mother found a jewel who hated Hitler.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] we were quite sure that she would never, never, never, under pain of death, say anything she had heard.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "So we had substantial freedom inside the four walls of our own home.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "In school, I was no longer allowed to talk to my former friends, only the Jewish girls in the back row.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "We would-- the way the German school day was arranged, we had school for four hours, I believe, in the morning, with two recesses-- two or three.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "Then we went home for the big meal-- we ate a lot-- and then we came back at 2:00, and we had classes from 2:00 to 4:00, so that we had six hours a day of instruction.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "We went out to the schoolyard during the recesses, and we were no longer allowed to play with our friends.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "We were no longer allowed any kind of contact.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And all of this culminated into one of the worst days of my life.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "May I talk about the picnic?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] We-- as in America, at the end of a school year, the school year in Germany ends before Easter.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "In other words, March, April, depending on when Easter is.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
